<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-09-22T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-09-22T18:00:00-05:00" n="1446" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1446">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">702.4193/9–2249: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Callanan</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-09-22T19:00:00-04:00">September
                                    22, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>92. Fol instrs supplement those contained Deptel 74, Sept 1<note n="11" xml:id="d1446fn11">Not printed.</note> and previous.</p>
                        <p>I. Brit have agreed afford US cits Hankow protection (Deptel 2961 Aug 18
                            to London<note n="12" xml:id="d1446fn12">
                                <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1320">p.
                                1320</ref>.</note> sent Hankow 62). Specifically Dept has asked Brit
                            perform fol services for Amcits: Financial assistance; welfare
                            whereabouts; in case physical danger or distress render all possible
                            assistance persons previously documented as Amcits; reports of death;
                            conservation personal property; reports of birth upon request; notarials
                            on an accommodation basis. Will require no visa or passport
                            services.</p>
                        <p>[Here follow detailed instructions.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>